Idea: Spaces where memories slowly grow dull as they're absorbed by nearby Fracturing Fissures. A dark cyan tint fills the room as the air vibrates a sickening 2413Hz frequency.
Fracuting Zones are ghost-like spaces where the Fracturing bleeds into reality. They have several tiers that affect how strong the zone is, and what kinds of occurances can happen within.

Tier 0
Fissures: 1
When a single fissure is made, it's mostly meant merely to contain an archkin, or other similar frequency-attuned creature, on the spot.
It carries no other major threat, unless a vicar arrives to summon reinforcements from it in the form of Fracturing Caradels.

Tier 1
Fissures: 2-3
This is when the ambiance starts shifting the cyan as fissure flies float around. It becomes easier to call in more caradels as the zone itself passively fabricates point caradels.

Tier 2
4-8 Fissures
Locus and Polygonal Caradels start passively fabricating around the fissures as the air starts vibrating.

Tier 3
9-15 Fissures
Rogue Caradels can now spawn passively.

Tier 4
16-20
FissureQuakes can now happen as Thronus caradels can now control the terrain. Fissure Quakes happen when a Thronus arrives and leaves. The quake takes rooms and other small spaces in the zone, and swaps them around one-another.
